---
title: Chicken Sausage & Mushroom Flatbreads with Garlicky White Sauce & Mozzarella
description: Move over, marinara—there’s a new sauce in town! These crispy flatbreads are spread with a creamy, garlicky white sauce we just can’t get enough of. We top them with a mix of jammy caramelized shallot, mushrooms, and tomato, then sprinkle generously with melty mozzarella and tangy goat cheese crumbles. Sure, we love our marinara, but for a break from tradition, try this delicious 30-minute departure (a fantastic dinner idea if we’ve ever heard of one).
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/63ed2113b25d0d79b30e6379-c0b5623e.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/chicken-sausage-mushroom-flatbreads-63ed2113b25d0d79b30e6379-909a7195.pdf
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/chicken-sausage-mushroom-flatbreads-63ed2113b25d0d79b30e6379
time required: 30 minutes
cuisine: Italian
nutrition:
  calories: 870 kcal
  fat: 44 g
  saturated fat: 17 g
  carbohydrates: 74 g
  sugar: 12 g
  protein: 46 g
  fiber: 4 g
  sodium: 2240 mg
author: HelloFresh
servings: 2
course: main course
---

Adjust rack to top position (top and middle positions for 4 servings) and preheat oven to 450 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Dice @tomato{1} into ½-inch pieces. Trim and thinly slice @button mushrooms{4%ounce} (skip if your mushrooms are pre-sliced!). Halve, peel, and thinly slice @shallot{1}. Peel and grate @garlic{1%clove} using a #zester{}.

In a #large bowl{}, combine tomato, a drizzle of @olive oil{1%teaspoon}, ½ tsp @Italian seasoning{1%tablespoon}, @salt{} and @pepper{}. (You'll use more Italian Seasoning later.) Set aside to marinate.

Place @flatbreads{2} on a #baking sheet{}; toast on top rack until lightly browned, ~{5-7%minutes}. (For 4 servings, divide between two sheets; toast on top and middle racks, swapping rack positions halfway through.)

Pat chicken dry with paper towels. Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{2%teaspoon} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add @Italian chicken sausage mix{9%ounce}; cook, stirring frequently, until browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes}. Turn off heat; transfer to a #plate{} and cover to keep warm. Wipe out pan.

While flatbreads toast, heat a drizzle of oil in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add mushrooms and shallot; season with ¼ tsp salt (½ tsp for 4 servings) and pepper. Cook, stirring frequently, until lightly browned and softened, ~{5-7%minutes}.

Stir in @sugar{½%teaspoon} (1 tsp for 4) and a splash of water. Cook, stirring, until mixture is caramelized and jammy, ~{1-2%minutes} more.

Turn off heat; transfer to #bowl{} with tomato and toss to combine. Wipe out pan.

> Use pan used for chicken or sausage here.

Melt @butter{1%tablespoon} (2 TBSP for 4 servings) in same pan over medium-high heat. Add garlic and @flour{1%tablespoon}. Cook, whisking constantly, until lightly browned and fragrant, ~{30%seconds}.

Reduce heat to medium low; whisk in @cream cheese{2%tablespoon} and @water{½%cup} (1 cup for 4) until melted and combined. Add 1 tsp @Italian seasoning{1%tablespoon} (2 tsp for 4); season generously with salt and pepper. Bring to a simmer; cook, stirring occasionally, until thickened, ~{1-2%minutes}. Remove from heat.

Heat broiler to high.

Evenly top flatbreads with white sauce and veggies. Sprinkle with @mozzarella cheese{½%cup} and crumble @goat cheese{1%ounce} over top.

Top flatbreads with chicken or sausage along with veggies.

Broil flatbreads until cheese melts, ~{1-2%minutes}. (For 4 servings, broil in batches.)

> Watch carefully to avoid burning.

Slice flatbreads into pieces. Divide between plates and serve.

> Chicken Sausage is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.